  "prompt": "Why is Quora flooded with questions on iit and iim only?",
  "response": "There are several reasons why Quora seems to be flooded with questions about IITs (Indian Institutes of Technology) and IIMs (Indian Institutes of Management):\n\n1. Popularity and Prestige\n- These are among the most prestigious educational institutions in India\n- They are highly competitive and difficult to get into\n- Many students aspire to study at these institutes\n\n2. Career Opportunities\n- IITs and IIMs are known for providing excellent job prospects\n- Graduates often receive high-paying jobs in top companies\n- Many people seek advice about admission, preparation, and career paths\n\n3. Large Student Population\n- India has a huge young population interested in engineering and management\n- Many students use Quora to seek guidance and information\n- These platforms become natural discussion spaces\n\n4. Cultural Significance\n- These institutes are seen as symbols of academic excellence in India\n- Getting into an IIT or IIM is often considered a significant achievement\n- Social and familial expectations contribute to the heightened interest\n\n5. User Demographics\n- Quora's user base in India is predominantly young and education-focused\n- Many users are students or recent graduates\n- They actively engage in discussions about education and career\n\n6. Content Ecosystem\n- More questions attract more answers\n- Existing content generates further interest and more related queries\n\nThese factors contribute to the seemingly disproportionate number of questions about IITs and IIMs on Quora.",
